# Branding & Design System (Portfolio)

## Source of Truth

**ALWAYS refer to `docs/branding-guide.html` for the exact tokens, typography, and component styling.**

This replaces the prior pixel-art guide. The portfolio site is **professional and employer-facing**.

> Why tokens: CSS custom properties let you define design values once and reuse them everywhere for consistency and fast updates. (This is the intended use of CSS custom properties.)  

## Brand Goals

- **Credible + readable** (journalism/research)
- **Proof-forward** (artifacts beat claims)
- **Scannable** (employer skim in <30 seconds)
- **Accessible** (keyboard focus visible; contrast meets WCAG minimums)

## Design Token Rules

### Token naming
Use **semantic tokens** (what the color *means*), not literal names (e.g., avoid `--gold-500` in components).

**Required tokens** (match HTML):
- `--bg`, `--surface`, `--surface-2`
- `--text`, `--muted`, `--border`
- `--brand`, `--brand-ink`
- `--info`, `--success`, `--warning`, `--danger`
- `--focus`, `--focus-outer`

> Keep these declared in `:root`. Optional theme switching can be done with `[data-theme="dark"]`.

### Accessibility minimums
- Text contrast should meet **WCAG 1.4.3** (4.5:1 normal text, 3:1 large text).
- Focus indicators should be clearly visible (WCAG 2.2 focus appearance guidance).

**Focus style (required):**
- Use `:focus-visible` with a 3px outline + 2px offset and an outer glow.
- Do not remove outlines.

## Typography

- **Headings:** `Newsreader` (serif) for credibility / editorial feel.
- **Body/UI:** `Inter` for clean UI readability.

**Hierarchy:**
- H1: serif, 36–48px
- H2: serif, 24–32px
- Body: 16–18px, line-height 1.6–1.8
- Meta/captions: 12–14px, muted

## Layout Standards

- Max content width: `1100px`
- Default page padding: `20px`
- Sections: 40–64px vertical spacing
- Cards: radius 14px, 1px border, soft shadow

## Components

### Buttons (required variants)

Base class: `.btn`
- Inline-flex, 10px/14px padding, radius 12px, font-weight 600
- `:active` translates down 1px
- Hover: subtle (no dramatic motion)

Variants:
- `.btn-primary` — **Brand** CTA (gold). Use sparingly (1 primary action per section).
- `.btn-secondary` — Outline / neutral.
- `.btn-ghost` — Minimal emphasis.
- `.btn-danger` — Destructive only.

### Cards
- `.card` — elevated card with shadow (use for major sections)
- `.card-flat` — flat card (lists, small panels)

### Pills / Tags
- `.pill` — small tag for: tools, years, role types, categories.
- Keep tags factual (no hype like “elite” or “unmatched”).

### Form fields
- `.field` — 12px radius, 1px border, clear placeholder, strong focus ring.

## Content rules (employer-facing)

- Prefer **measurable facts** + supporting artifacts:
  - Journalism: clip links + date + outlet
  - Research: poster, abstract, role, tooling (E-Prime)
  - Ops: budgets/workflows + award photo
- Avoid fluff adjectives (“passionate”, “hardworking”) unless backed by evidence.
- Avoid jargon and startup-speak.

## Tailwind mapping (if using Tailwind theme tokens)

If you're using Tailwind theme variables, map them to CSS variables:

- `bg-[color:var(--bg)]`
- `text-[color:var(--text)]`
- `border-[color:var(--border)]`
- For buttons, prefer component classes (`btn btn-primary`) to keep styling centralized.

## Do / Don’t

✅ DO
- Keep 1 primary CTA per page section
- Use consistent spacing + headings
- Ensure keyboard focus is visible everywhere

❌ DON’T
- Use heavy gradients, neon palettes, or noisy backgrounds
- Use more than 2 typefaces
- Add “stats” you cannot defend
